children.subject: Tbh no class at Cal is worth the trouble, since everything can be learnt just as well online/at home. But jobs need "degrees" so here we are.
(idk about grad courses, talking with regards to undergrad ones)

Worrying will serve you in no way. You will be able to enroll eventually. 162 is overrated anyways, self studying is sufficient after taking 61c and a couple of the other 16x classes. It's a class that's not worth the trouble.

history.content: Not really. Of course, there are courses where seniors have much higher chance over juniors but deal with it, you will become a senior one day. Generally, if you really want to get into classes, you will most likely get in. That means, you have to understand how enrollment works and how to best strategize to maximize your chance of enrollment. Take 162 as an example, seeing that data8 (also had room scheduling issues) opened a few days ago and that 162 was announced to be available sometimes by the end of the week, it would make sense to pay close attention to the piazza page on Friday to get the most updated status on the class. The class filled up in 7 hours, not instantly.
